performers: Dean Wareham - guitar/vocals|Naomi Yang - bass/vocals|Damon Krukowski - drums
notes: Galaxie 500's first ever show.At summer's end we played a gig at my apartment on Front Street. Naomi made up little flyers for the event.It was the best gig of my life. I didn't break a string. I didn't forget the words. We played for 20 minutes, and it was just perfect.Dean Wareham, Black Postcards. Penguin Press; 2008.we definitely played "Knockin' on Heaven's Door" and likely "Walking Song" and "On the Floor" and possibly "Where Have all the Flowers Gone" and "I Can See Clearly Now the Rain is Gone" Dean Wareham (@WarehamDean), 29th August 2019
